7)Describe a Challenge You Faced and How You Solved It
We faced a production issue where the Kafka consumer lag was increasing and messages were processing slowly.
On analysis, we noticed frequent consumer rebalancing during peak traffic.
The root cause was a large batch size and low poll interval, causing processing to exceed the poll timeout.
Kafka assumed the consumer was unhealthy and kept rebalancing.
To fix this, we reduced the batch size using max.poll.records from 500 to 100.
We also increased max.poll.interval.ms from 60000(1 min) to 300000(5 min)to match the actual processing time.
Additionally, we disabled auto-commit to commit offsets only after successful processing.
We tested the changes in lower environments and monitored lag metrics.
After deployment, consumer lag reduced and message processing became stable.

